		<strong><h1><br>
		<p>Egypt </p></h1></strong>
		<div><h4>Egyptian cuisine makes heavy use of legumes, vegetables and fruit from Egypt's rich Nile Valley and Delta. 
										Examples of Egyptian dishes include rice-stuffed vegetables and grape leaves, hummus, falafel, shawarma, kebab and kofta. ful medames, 
										mashed fava beans; kushari, lentils and pasta; and molokhiya, bush okra stew. A local type of pita bread known as eish baladi 
										(Egyptian Arabic: عيش بلدي) is a staple of Egyptian cuisine, and cheesemaking in Egypt dates back to the First Dynasty of Egypt, with domty 
										being the most popular type of cheese consumed today.Common meats in Egyptian cuisine are squab, chicken, and lamb.Lamb and beef 
										are frequently used for grilling. Offal is a popular fast food in cities, and foie gras is a delicacy that has been prepared in the region since at least 2500 BCE.
										Fish and seafood are common in Egypt's coastal regions.</h4>
